{
  "Question": "<p>I have been working on this limit for days, but I am not getting it. The question is</p> <blockquote> <p>Compute the limit <span class=\"math-container\" id=\"q_105\"><math alttext=\"\\lim_{t\\to+\\infty}\\int_{0}^{+\\infty}\\frac{\\mathrm{d}x}{e^{x}+\\sin(tx)}\" class=\"ltx_Math\" display=\"inline\" xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><semantics><mrow><msub><mo>lim</mo><mrow><mi>t</mi><mo>\u2192</mo><mrow><mo>+</mo><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">\u221e</mi></mrow></mrow></msub><mo>\u2061</mo><mrow><msubsup><mo largeop=\"true\" symmetric=\"true\">\u222b</mo><mn>0</mn><mrow><mo>+</mo><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">\u221e</mi></mrow></msubsup><mfrac><mrow><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">d</mi><mo>\u2062</mo><mi>x</mi></mrow><mrow><msup><mi>e</mi><mi>x</mi></msup><mo>+</mo><mrow><mi>sin</mi><mo>\u2061</mo><mrow><mo stretchy=\"false\">(</mo><mrow><mi>t</mi><mo>\u2062</mo><mi>x</mi></mrow><mo stretchy=\"false\">)</mo></mrow></mrow></mrow></mfrac></mrow></mrow></semantics></math></span></p> </blockquote> <p>Note that the integral is well defined and convergent for every <span class=\"math-container\" id=\"q_106\"><math alttext=\"t&gt;0\" class=\"ltx_Math\" display=\"inline\" xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><semantics><mrow><mi>t</mi><mo>&gt;</mo><mn>0</mn></mrow></semantics></math></span>. Indeed the integrand function is a positive function for every <span class=\"math-container\" id=\"q_107\"><math alttext=\"t&gt;0\" class=\"ltx_Math\" display=\"inline\" xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><semantics><mrow><mi>t</mi><mo>&gt;</mo><mn>0</mn></mrow></semantics></math></span> since <span class=\"math-container\" id=\"q_108\"><math alttext=\"e^{x}+\\sin tx&gt;e^{x}-1&gt;x&gt;0\" class=\"ltx_Math\" display=\"inline\" xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><semantics><mrow><mrow><msup><mi>e</mi><mi>x</mi></msup><mo>+</mo><mrow><mi>sin</mi><mo>\u2061</mo><mrow><mi>t</mi><mo>\u2062</mo><mi>x</mi></mrow></mrow></mrow><mo>&gt;</mo><mrow><msup><mi>e</mi><mi>x</mi></msup><mo>-</mo><mn>1</mn></mrow><mo>&gt;</mo><mi>x</mi><mo>&gt;</mo><mn>0</mn></mrow></semantics></math></span> And as <span class=\"math-container\" id=\"q_109\"><math alttext=\"x\\to+\\infty\" class=\"ltx_Math\" display=\"inline\" xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><semantics><mrow><mi>x</mi><mo>\u2192</mo><mrow><mo>+</mo><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">\u221e</mi></mrow></mrow></semantics></math></span> the integrand function behaves like <span class=\"math-container\" id=\"q_110\"><math alttext=\"e^{-x}\" class=\"ltx_Math\" display=\"inline\" xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><semantics><msup><mi>e</mi><mrow><mo>-</mo><mi>x</mi></mrow></msup></semantics></math></span>.</p> <p>WHAT I TRIED:</p> <p>I consider <span class=\"math-container\" id=\"q_111\"><math alttext=\"t=2n\\pi\" class=\"ltx_Math\" display=\"inline\" xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><semantics><mrow><mi>t</mi><mo>=</mo><mrow><mn>2</mn><mo>\u2062</mo><mi>n</mi><mo>\u2062</mo><mi>\u03c0</mi></mrow></mrow></semantics></math></span> a multiple of <span class=\"math-container\" id=\"q_112\"><math alttext=\"2\\pi\" class=\"ltx_Math\" display=\"inline\" xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><semantics><mrow><mn>2</mn><mo>\u2062</mo><mi>\u03c0</mi></mrow></semantics></math></span>, and see what happens: <span class=\"math-container\" id=\"q_113\"><math alttext=\"\\int_{0}^{+\\infty}\\frac{\\mathrm{d}x}{e^{x}+\\sin(2n\\pi x)}=\\sum_{k=0}^{\\infty}% \\int_{k/n}^{(k+1)/n}\\frac{\\mathrm{d}x}{e^{x}+\\sin(2n\\pi x)}\" class=\"ltx_Math\" display=\"inline\" xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><semantics><mrow><mrow><msubsup><mo largeop=\"true\" symmetric=\"true\">\u222b</mo><mn>0</mn><mrow><mo>+</mo><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">\u221e</mi></mrow></msubsup><mfrac><mrow><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">d</mi><mo>\u2062</mo><mi>x</mi></mrow><mrow><msup><mi>e</mi><mi>x</mi></msup><mo>+</mo><mrow><mi>sin</mi><mo>\u2061</mo><mrow><mo stretchy=\"false\">(</mo><mrow><mn>2</mn><mo>\u2062</mo><mi>n</mi><mo>\u2062</mo><mi>\u03c0</mi><mo>\u2062</mo><mi>x</mi></mrow><mo stretchy=\"false\">)</mo></mrow></mrow></mrow></mfrac></mrow><mo>=</mo><mrow><msubsup><mo largeop=\"true\" symmetric=\"true\">\u2211</mo><mrow><mi>k</mi><mo>=</mo><mn>0</mn></mrow><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">\u221e</mi></msubsup><mrow><msubsup><mo largeop=\"true\" symmetric=\"true\">\u222b</mo><mrow><mi>k</mi><mo>/</mo><mi>n</mi></mrow><mrow><mrow><mo stretchy=\"false\">(</mo><mrow><mi>k</mi><mo>+</mo><mn>1</mn></mrow><mo stretchy=\"false\">)</mo></mrow><mo>/</mo><mi>n</mi></mrow></msubsup><mfrac><mrow><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">d</mi><mo>\u2062</mo><mi>x</mi></mrow><mrow><msup><mi>e</mi><mi>x</mi></msup><mo>+</mo><mrow><mi>sin</mi><mo>\u2061</mo><mrow><mo stretchy=\"false\">(</mo><mrow><mn>2</mn><mo>\u2062</mo><mi>n</mi><mo>\u2062</mo><mi>\u03c0</mi><mo>\u2062</mo><mi>x</mi></mrow><mo stretchy=\"false\">)</mo></mrow></mrow></mrow></mfrac></mrow></mrow></mrow></semantics></math></span> Making the change of variables <span class=\"math-container\" id=\"q_114\"><math alttext=\"u=2n\\pi x\" class=\"ltx_Math\" display=\"inline\" xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><semantics><mrow><mi>u</mi><mo>=</mo><mrow><mn>2</mn><mo>\u2062</mo><mi>n</mi><mo>\u2062</mo><mi>\u03c0</mi><mo>\u2062</mo><mi>x</mi></mrow></mrow></semantics></math></span> I get <span class=\"math-container\" id=\"q_115\"><math alttext=\"\\begin{aligned} \\displaystyle\\sum_{k=0}^{\\infty}\\frac{1}{2n\\pi}\\int_{2k\\pi}^{(% 2k+2)\\pi}\\frac{\\mathrm{d}u}{e^{u/2n\\pi}+\\sin(u)}&amp;\\displaystyle\\geq\\sum_{k=0}^{% \\infty}\\frac{1}{2n\\pi}\\int_{2k\\pi}^{(2k+2)\\pi}\\frac{\\mathrm{d}u}{e^{(2k+2)\\pi/% 2n\\pi}+\\sin(u)}\\\\ &amp;\\displaystyle=\\sum_{k=0}^{\\infty}\\frac{1}{2n\\pi}\\int_{2k\\pi}^{(2k+2)\\pi}\\frac% {\\mathrm{d}u}{e^{(k+1)/n}+\\sin(u)}\\end{aligned}\" class=\"ltx_Math\" display=\"inline\" xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><semantics><mtable columnspacing=\"0pt\" rowspacing=\"0pt\"><mtr><mtd columnalign=\"right\"><mrow><mstyle displaystyle=\"true\"><munderover><mo largeop=\"true\" movablelimits=\"false\" symmetric=\"true\">\u2211</mo><mrow><mi>k</mi><mo>=</mo><mn>0</mn></mrow><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">\u221e</mi></munderover></mstyle><mrow><mstyle displaystyle=\"true\"><mfrac><mn>1</mn><mrow><mn>2</mn><mo>\u2062</mo><mi>n</mi><mo>\u2062</mo><mi>\u03c0</mi></mrow></mfrac></mstyle><mo>\u2062</mo><mrow><mstyle displaystyle=\"true\"><msubsup><mo largeop=\"true\" symmetric=\"true\">\u222b</mo><mrow><mn>2</mn><mo>\u2062</mo><mi>k</mi><mo>\u2062</mo><mi>\u03c0</mi></mrow><mrow><mrow><mo stretchy=\"false\">(</mo><mrow><mrow><mn>2</mn><mo>\u2062</mo><mi>k</mi></mrow><mo>+</mo><mn>2</mn></mrow><mo stretchy=\"false\">)</mo></mrow><mo>\u2062</mo><mi>\u03c0</mi></mrow></msubsup></mstyle><mstyle displaystyle=\"true\"><mfrac><mrow><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">d</mi><mo>\u2062</mo><mi>u</mi></mrow><mrow><msup><mi>e</mi><mrow><mrow><mi>u</mi><mo>/</mo><mn>2</mn></mrow><mo>\u2062</mo><mi>n</mi><mo>\u2062</mo><mi>\u03c0</mi></mrow></msup><mo>+</mo><mrow><mi>sin</mi><mo>\u2061</mo><mrow><mo stretchy=\"false\">(</mo><mi>u</mi><mo stretchy=\"false\">)</mo></mrow></mrow></mrow></mfrac></mstyle></mrow></mrow></mrow></mtd><mtd columnalign=\"left\"><mrow><mi></mi><mo>\u2265</mo><mrow><mstyle displaystyle=\"true\"><munderover><mo largeop=\"true\" movablelimits=\"false\" symmetric=\"true\">\u2211</mo><mrow><mi>k</mi><mo>=</mo><mn>0</mn></mrow><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">\u221e</mi></munderover></mstyle><mrow><mstyle displaystyle=\"true\"><mfrac><mn>1</mn><mrow><mn>2</mn><mo>\u2062</mo><mi>n</mi><mo>\u2062</mo><mi>\u03c0</mi></mrow></mfrac></mstyle><mo>\u2062</mo><mrow><mstyle displaystyle=\"true\"><msubsup><mo largeop=\"true\" symmetric=\"true\">\u222b</mo><mrow><mn>2</mn><mo>\u2062</mo><mi>k</mi><mo>\u2062</mo><mi>\u03c0</mi></mrow><mrow><mrow><mo stretchy=\"false\">(</mo><mrow><mrow><mn>2</mn><mo>\u2062</mo><mi>k</mi></mrow><mo>+</mo><mn>2</mn></mrow><mo stretchy=\"false\">)</mo></mrow><mo>\u2062</mo><mi>\u03c0</mi></mrow></msubsup></mstyle><mstyle displaystyle=\"true\"><mfrac><mrow><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">d</mi><mo>\u2062</mo><mi>u</mi></mrow><mrow><msup><mi>e</mi><mrow><mrow><mrow><mrow><mo stretchy=\"false\">(</mo><mrow><mrow><mn>2</mn><mo>\u2062</mo><mi>k</mi></mrow><mo>+</mo><mn>2</mn></mrow><mo stretchy=\"false\">)</mo></mrow><mo>\u2062</mo><mi>\u03c0</mi></mrow><mo>/</mo><mn>2</mn></mrow><mo>\u2062</mo><mi>n</mi><mo>\u2062</mo><mi>\u03c0</mi></mrow></msup><mo>+</mo><mrow><mi>sin</mi><mo>\u2061</mo><mrow><mo stretchy=\"false\">(</mo><mi>u</mi><mo stretchy=\"false\">)</mo></mrow></mrow></mrow></mfrac></mstyle></mrow></mrow></mrow></mrow></mtd></mtr><mtr><mtd></mtd><mtd columnalign=\"left\"><mrow><mi></mi><mo>=</mo><mrow><mstyle displaystyle=\"true\"><munderover><mo largeop=\"true\" movablelimits=\"false\" symmetric=\"true\">\u2211</mo><mrow><mi>k</mi><mo>=</mo><mn>0</mn></mrow><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">\u221e</mi></munderover></mstyle><mrow><mstyle displaystyle=\"true\"><mfrac><mn>1</mn><mrow><mn>2</mn><mo>\u2062</mo><mi>n</mi><mo>\u2062</mo><mi>\u03c0</mi></mrow></mfrac></mstyle><mo>\u2062</mo><mrow><mstyle displaystyle=\"true\"><msubsup><mo largeop=\"true\" symmetric=\"true\">\u222b</mo><mrow><mn>2</mn><mo>\u2062</mo><mi>k</mi><mo>\u2062</mo><mi>\u03c0</mi></mrow><mrow><mrow><mo stretchy=\"false\">(</mo><mrow><mrow><mn>2</mn><mo>\u2062</mo><mi>k</mi></mrow><mo>+</mo><mn>2</mn></mrow><mo stretchy=\"false\">)</mo></mrow><mo>\u2062</mo><mi>\u03c0</mi></mrow></msubsup></mstyle><mstyle displaystyle=\"true\"><mfrac><mrow><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">d</mi><mo>\u2062</mo><mi>u</mi></mrow><mrow><msup><mi>e</mi><mrow><mrow><mo stretchy=\"false\">(</mo><mrow><mi>k</mi><mo>+</mo><mn>1</mn></mrow><mo stretchy=\"false\">)</mo></mrow><mo>/</mo><mi>n</mi></mrow></msup><mo>+</mo><mrow><mi>sin</mi><mo>\u2061</mo><mrow><mo stretchy=\"false\">(</mo><mi>u</mi><mo stretchy=\"false\">)</mo></mrow></mrow></mrow></mfrac></mstyle></mrow></mrow></mrow></mrow></mtd></mtr></mtable></semantics></math></span> where I write the lower bound with the minimum of the function at <span class=\"math-container\" id=\"q_116\"><math alttext=\"u=(2k+2)\\pi\" class=\"ltx_Math\" display=\"inline\" xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><semantics><mrow><mi>u</mi><mo>=</mo><mrow><mrow><mo stretchy=\"false\">(</mo><mrow><mrow><mn>2</mn><mo>\u2062</mo><mi>k</mi></mrow><mo>+</mo><mn>2</mn></mrow><mo stretchy=\"false\">)</mo></mrow><mo>\u2062</mo><mi>\u03c0</mi></mrow></mrow></semantics></math></span>. Now I use the fact that the integrand function does is integrated over a period of <span class=\"math-container\" id=\"q_117\"><math alttext=\"2\\pi\" class=\"ltx_Math\" display=\"inline\" xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><semantics><mrow><mn>2</mn><mo>\u2062</mo><mi>\u03c0</mi></mrow></semantics></math></span>, and using the result for <span class=\"math-container\" id=\"q_118\"><math alttext=\"C&gt;1\" class=\"ltx_Math\" display=\"inline\" xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><semantics><mrow><mi>C</mi><mo>&gt;</mo><mn>1</mn></mrow></semantics></math></span> <span class=\"math-container\" id=\"q_119\"><math alttext=\"\\int_{0}^{2\\pi}\\frac{\\mathrm{d}u}{C+\\sin(u)}=\\frac{2\\pi}{\\sqrt{C^{2}-1}}\" class=\"ltx_Math\" display=\"inline\" xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><semantics><mrow><mrow><msubsup><mo largeop=\"true\" symmetric=\"true\">\u222b</mo><mn>0</mn><mrow><mn>2</mn><mo>\u2062</mo><mi>\u03c0</mi></mrow></msubsup><mfrac><mrow><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">d</mi><mo>\u2062</mo><mi>u</mi></mrow><mrow><mi>C</mi><mo>+</mo><mrow><mi>sin</mi><mo>\u2061</mo><mrow><mo stretchy=\"false\">(</mo><mi>u</mi><mo stretchy=\"false\">)</mo></mrow></mrow></mrow></mfrac></mrow><mo>=</mo><mfrac><mrow><mn>2</mn><mo>\u2062</mo><mi>\u03c0</mi></mrow><msqrt><mrow><msup><mi>C</mi><mn>2</mn></msup><mo>-</mo><mn>1</mn></mrow></msqrt></mfrac></mrow></semantics></math></span> I get the estimate <span class=\"math-container\" id=\"q_120\"><math alttext=\"\\begin{aligned} \\displaystyle\\sum_{k=0}^{\\infty}\\frac{1}{2n\\pi}\\int_{2k\\pi}^{(% 2k+2)\\pi}\\frac{\\mathrm{d}u}{e^{(k+1)/n}+\\sin(u)}&amp;\\displaystyle=\\sum_{k=0}^{% \\infty}\\frac{1}{2n\\pi}\\frac{2\\pi}{\\sqrt{e^{2(k+1)/n}-1}}\\\\ &amp;\\displaystyle=\\frac{1}{n}\\sum_{k=0}^{\\infty}\\frac{1}{\\sqrt{e^{2(k+1)/n}-1}}% \\end{aligned}\" class=\"ltx_Math\" display=\"inline\" xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><semantics><mtable columnspacing=\"0pt\" rowspacing=\"0pt\"><mtr><mtd columnalign=\"right\"><mrow><mstyle displaystyle=\"true\"><munderover><mo largeop=\"true\" movablelimits=\"false\" symmetric=\"true\">\u2211</mo><mrow><mi>k</mi><mo>=</mo><mn>0</mn></mrow><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">\u221e</mi></munderover></mstyle><mrow><mstyle displaystyle=\"true\"><mfrac><mn>1</mn><mrow><mn>2</mn><mo>\u2062</mo><mi>n</mi><mo>\u2062</mo><mi>\u03c0</mi></mrow></mfrac></mstyle><mo>\u2062</mo><mrow><mstyle displaystyle=\"true\"><msubsup><mo largeop=\"true\" symmetric=\"true\">\u222b</mo><mrow><mn>2</mn><mo>\u2062</mo><mi>k</mi><mo>\u2062</mo><mi>\u03c0</mi></mrow><mrow><mrow><mo stretchy=\"false\">(</mo><mrow><mrow><mn>2</mn><mo>\u2062</mo><mi>k</mi></mrow><mo>+</mo><mn>2</mn></mrow><mo stretchy=\"false\">)</mo></mrow><mo>\u2062</mo><mi>\u03c0</mi></mrow></msubsup></mstyle><mstyle displaystyle=\"true\"><mfrac><mrow><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">d</mi><mo>\u2062</mo><mi>u</mi></mrow><mrow><msup><mi>e</mi><mrow><mrow><mo stretchy=\"false\">(</mo><mrow><mi>k</mi><mo>+</mo><mn>1</mn></mrow><mo stretchy=\"false\">)</mo></mrow><mo>/</mo><mi>n</mi></mrow></msup><mo>+</mo><mrow><mi>sin</mi><mo>\u2061</mo><mrow><mo stretchy=\"false\">(</mo><mi>u</mi><mo stretchy=\"false\">)</mo></mrow></mrow></mrow></mfrac></mstyle></mrow></mrow></mrow></mtd><mtd columnalign=\"left\"><mrow><mi></mi><mo>=</mo><mrow><mstyle displaystyle=\"true\"><munderover><mo largeop=\"true\" movablelimits=\"false\" symmetric=\"true\">\u2211</mo><mrow><mi>k</mi><mo>=</mo><mn>0</mn></mrow><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">\u221e</mi></munderover></mstyle><mrow><mstyle displaystyle=\"true\"><mfrac><mn>1</mn><mrow><mn>2</mn><mo>\u2062</mo><mi>n</mi><mo>\u2062</mo><mi>\u03c0</mi></mrow></mfrac></mstyle><mo>\u2062</mo><mstyle displaystyle=\"true\"><mfrac><mrow><mn>2</mn><mo>\u2062</mo><mi>\u03c0</mi></mrow><msqrt><mrow><msup><mi>e</mi><mrow><mrow><mn>2</mn><mo>\u2062</mo><mrow><mo stretchy=\"false\">(</mo><mrow><mi>k</mi><mo>+</mo><mn>1</mn></mrow><mo stretchy=\"false\">)</mo></mrow></mrow><mo>/</mo><mi>n</mi></mrow></msup><mo>-</mo><mn>1</mn></mrow></msqrt></mfrac></mstyle></mrow></mrow></mrow></mtd></mtr><mtr><mtd></mtd><mtd columnalign=\"left\"><mrow><mi></mi><mo>=</mo><mrow><mstyle displaystyle=\"true\"><mfrac><mn>1</mn><mi>n</mi></mfrac></mstyle><mo>\u2062</mo><mrow><mstyle displaystyle=\"true\"><munderover><mo largeop=\"true\" movablelimits=\"false\" symmetric=\"true\">\u2211</mo><mrow><mi>k</mi><mo>=</mo><mn>0</mn></mrow><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">\u221e</mi></munderover></mstyle><mstyle displaystyle=\"true\"><mfrac><mn>1</mn><msqrt><mrow><msup><mi>e</mi><mrow><mrow><mn>2</mn><mo>\u2062</mo><mrow><mo stretchy=\"false\">(</mo><mrow><mi>k</mi><mo>+</mo><mn>1</mn></mrow><mo stretchy=\"false\">)</mo></mrow></mrow><mo>/</mo><mi>n</mi></mrow></msup><mo>-</mo><mn>1</mn></mrow></msqrt></mfrac></mstyle></mrow></mrow></mrow></mtd></mtr></mtable></semantics></math></span> Summing all up, I got that <span class=\"math-container\" id=\"q_121\"><math alttext=\"\\int_{0}^{+\\infty}\\frac{\\mathrm{d}x}{e^{x}+\\sin(2n\\pi x)}\\geq\\frac{1}{n}\\sum_{% k=0}^{\\infty}\\frac{1}{\\sqrt{e^{2(k+1)/n}-1}}\" class=\"ltx_Math\" display=\"inline\" xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><semantics><mrow><mrow><msubsup><mo largeop=\"true\" symmetric=\"true\">\u222b</mo><mn>0</mn><mrow><mo>+</mo><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">\u221e</mi></mrow></msubsup><mfrac><mrow><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">d</mi><mo>\u2062</mo><mi>x</mi></mrow><mrow><msup><mi>e</mi><mi>x</mi></msup><mo>+</mo><mrow><mi>sin</mi><mo>\u2061</mo><mrow><mo stretchy=\"false\">(</mo><mrow><mn>2</mn><mo>\u2062</mo><mi>n</mi><mo>\u2062</mo><mi>\u03c0</mi><mo>\u2062</mo><mi>x</mi></mrow><mo stretchy=\"false\">)</mo></mrow></mrow></mrow></mfrac></mrow><mo>\u2265</mo><mrow><mfrac><mn>1</mn><mi>n</mi></mfrac><mo>\u2062</mo><mrow><msubsup><mo largeop=\"true\" symmetric=\"true\">\u2211</mo><mrow><mi>k</mi><mo>=</mo><mn>0</mn></mrow><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">\u221e</mi></msubsup><mfrac><mn>1</mn><msqrt><mrow><msup><mi>e</mi><mrow><mrow><mn>2</mn><mo>\u2062</mo><mrow><mo stretchy=\"false\">(</mo><mrow><mi>k</mi><mo>+</mo><mn>1</mn></mrow><mo stretchy=\"false\">)</mo></mrow></mrow><mo>/</mo><mi>n</mi></mrow></msup><mo>-</mo><mn>1</mn></mrow></msqrt></mfrac></mrow></mrow></mrow></semantics></math></span> As <span class=\"math-container\" id=\"q_122\"><math alttext=\"n\\to\\infty\" class=\"ltx_Math\" display=\"inline\" xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><semantics><mrow><mi>n</mi><mo>\u2192</mo><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">\u221e</mi></mrow></semantics></math></span> the series converges to the Riemann integral <span class=\"math-container\" id=\"q_123\"><math alttext=\"\\int_{0}^{+\\infty}\\frac{\\mathrm{d}y}{\\sqrt{e^{2y}-1}}=\\frac{\\pi}{2}\" class=\"ltx_Math\" display=\"inline\" xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><semantics><mrow><mrow><msubsup><mo largeop=\"true\" symmetric=\"true\">\u222b</mo><mn>0</mn><mrow><mo>+</mo><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">\u221e</mi></mrow></msubsup><mfrac><mrow><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">d</mi><mo>\u2062</mo><mi>y</mi></mrow><msqrt><mrow><msup><mi>e</mi><mrow><mn>2</mn><mo>\u2062</mo><mi>y</mi></mrow></msup><mo>-</mo><mn>1</mn></mrow></msqrt></mfrac></mrow><mo>=</mo><mfrac><mi>\u03c0</mi><mn>2</mn></mfrac></mrow></semantics></math></span></p> <p>Hence the limit should be a number larger than <span class=\"math-container\" id=\"q_124\"><math alttext=\"\\pi/2\" class=\"ltx_Math\" display=\"inline\" xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><semantics><mrow><mi>\u03c0</mi><mo>/</mo><mn>2</mn></mrow></semantics></math></span>, or <span class=\"math-container\" id=\"q_125\"><math alttext=\"+\\infty\" class=\"ltx_Math\" display=\"inline\" xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><semantics><mrow><mo>+</mo><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">\u221e</mi></mrow></semantics></math></span>.</p> <p>Using WA I got for large values of <span class=\"math-container\" id=\"q_126\"><math alttext=\"t\" class=\"ltx_Math\" display=\"inline\" xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><semantics><mi>t</mi></semantics></math></span> that the integral is between <span class=\"math-container\" id=\"q_127\"><math alttext=\"1\" class=\"ltx_Math\" display=\"inline\" xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><semantics><mn>1</mn></semantics></math></span> and <span class=\"math-container\" id=\"q_128\"><math alttext=\"2\" class=\"ltx_Math\" display=\"inline\" xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><semantics><mn>2</mn></semantics></math></span>, thus <span class=\"math-container\" id=\"q_129\"><math alttext=\"\\pi/2\" class=\"ltx_Math\" display=\"inline\" xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><semantics><mrow><mi>\u03c0</mi><mo>/</mo><mn>2</mn></mrow></semantics></math></span> could be the actual limit.</p>",
  "Title": "Compute the limit <span class=\"math-container\" id=\"q_104\"><math alttext=\"\\lim\\limits_{t\\to+\\infty}\\int_{0}^{+\\infty}\\frac{\\mathrm{d}x}{e^{x}+\\sin tx}\" class=\"ltx_Math\" display=\"inline\" xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><semantics><mrow><munder><mo movablelimits=\"false\">lim</mo><mrow><mi>t</mi><mo>\u2192</mo><mrow><mo>+</mo><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">\u221e</mi></mrow></mrow></munder><mo>\u2061</mo><mrow><msubsup><mo largeop=\"true\" symmetric=\"true\">\u222b</mo><mn>0</mn><mrow><mo>+</mo><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">\u221e</mi></mrow></msubsup><mfrac><mrow><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">d</mi><mo>\u2062</mo><mi>x</mi></mrow><mrow><msup><mi>e</mi><mi>x</mi></msup><mo>+</mo><mrow><mi>sin</mi><mo>\u2061</mo><mrow><mi>t</mi><mo>\u2062</mo><mi>x</mi></mrow></mrow></mrow></mfrac></mrow></mrow></semantics></math></span>",
